					<description><![CDATA[“Oak relief with garter stitch pull-over” (2024), oak, 115 x 115 x 9 centimeters. All images © Daniel Dewar and Grégory Gicquel, courtesy of Antenna Space, shared with permission The term “spoke” has traditionally referred to a piece of split log, like those used as supports in a wagon wheel. Traditional basket-making techniques draw on that [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>
<div id="attachment_246848" style="width: 1893px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-246848" class="wp-image-246848 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-9.jpg" alt="a wooden bas relief in oak of a knit sweater" width="1883" height="1920" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-9.jpg 1883w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-9-640x653.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-9-960x979.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-9-1506x1536.jpg 1506w" sizes="(max-width: 1883px) 100vw, 1883px"></p>
<p id="caption-attachment-246848" class="wp-caption-text">“Oak relief with garter stitch pull-over” (2024), oak, 115 x 115 x 9 centimeters. All images © Daniel Dewar and Grégory Gicquel, courtesy of Antenna Space, shared with permission</p>
</div>
<p>The term “spoke” has traditionally referred to a piece of split log, like those used as supports in a wagon wheel. Traditional basket-making techniques draw on that same concept by weaving flexible material through a stronger framework. For French artistic duo <a href="https://www.instagram.com/danieldewargregorygicquel/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Daniel Dewar and Grégory Gicquel</a>, notions of interlaced strands, patterns, ecosystems, and vessels shape their solo exhibition, <em>T</em><em>he Weaver and the Spoke,</em> at <a href="http://antenna-space.com/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Antenna Space</a> in Shanghai.</p>
<p><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Permaculture" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Permaculture</a>, a land management approach geared toward working with, rather than against nature, suffuses Dewar and Gicquel’s work, which often depicts animals and habitats coexisting alongside interspersed human-made elements. The chart-like quilts take cues from folk art or early natural history illustrations, where flora and fauna intermingle with items the artists employ in their studio, like thread and sewing machines. Knitted sweaters, woven loafers, and snail shells continue their interest in repetition, receptacles, and protective layers.</p>
<p>Dewar and Gicquel toy with the distinctions between art and function. The traditional purpose of quilts as bed coverings complements sculptures that double as storage, like in “Oak cabinet with woven loafer shoe and leg.” Hats and shoes nod to the garment industry, making a lighthearted comparison between textile’s pliable role throughout fine art, craft, apparel, and decorative arts.</p>
<p><em>The Weaver and the Spoke </em>continues through May 11. See more on the artists’ <a href="https://www.instagram.com/danieldewargregorygicquel/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram</a>.</p>
<p> </p>
<div id="attachment_246840" style="width: 1625px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-246840" class="wp-image-246840 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-1.jpg" alt="a quilt with patterns of flowers, grasshoppers, plants, a spool of thread, and worms on a light blue background" width="1615" height="1920" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-1.jpg 1615w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-1-640x761.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-1-960x1141.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-1-1292x1536.jpg 1292w" sizes="(max-width: 1615px) 100vw, 1615px"></p>
