</div>
<div id="attachment_246844" style="width: 1930px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-246844" class="wp-image-246844 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-5.jpg" alt="an oak bench carved with snail shells with a quilted cushion containing patterns of bugs and flowers" width="1920" height="1440" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-5.jpg 1920w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-5-640x480.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-5-960x720.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-5-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-5-285x214.jpg 285w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px"></p>
<p id="caption-attachment-246844" class="wp-caption-text">“Oak bench with white-tailed bumblebees, mallow flowers, dandelion flowers and snails” (2024), embroidery on cushion and oak, 60 x 146 x 66 centimeters</p>
</div>
<div id="attachment_246849" style="width: 1930px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-246849" class="wp-image-246849 size-full" src="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-2up.jpg" alt="two side-by-side images of a sculptural oak cabinet with baskets around the sides and a foot on top with a woven loafer" width="1920" height="1270" srcset="https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-2up.jpg 1920w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-2up-640x423.jpg 640w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-2up-960x635.jpg 960w, https://www.thisiscolossal.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/dewar-gicquel-2up-1536x1016.jpg 1536w" sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px"></p>
<p id="caption-attachment-246849" class="wp-caption-text">“Oak cabinet with woven loafer shoe and leg” (2024), oak, 155 x 65 x 56 centimeters</p>
</div>
